"{\"uid\": \"local3news.com-regional-national-dispute-over-jordan-chiles-olympic-floor-routine-rolls-on-as-us-claims-cas-sent-emails-article_edf71b17-f525-5727-b174-be6e82bf764b.html\", \"text\": \"Chattanooga  Cloudy  H42\\u00b0  L27\\u00b0  41\\u00b0  Altamont  Cloudy  H37\\u00b0  L23\\u00b0  34\\u00b0  Athens  Light Rain  H41\\u00b0  L29\\u00b0  40\\u00b0  Benton  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Chatsworth  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Cleveland  Cloudy  H42\\u00b0  L27\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Dalton  Fog  H43\\u00b0  L27\\u00b0  43\\u00b0  Dayton  Cloudy  H34\\u00b0  L22\\u00b0  32\\u00b0  Dunlap  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Murphy  Light Rain  H41\\u00b0  L29\\u00b0  40\\u00b0  Pikeville  Cloudy  H34\\u00b0  L22\\u00b0  32\\u00b0  Scottsboro  Cloudy  H37\\u00b0  L24\\u00b0  39\\u00b0  Summerville  Cloudy  H48\\u00b0  L30\\u00b0  47\\u00b0  Ringgold  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Trenton  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Chattanooga  Cloudy  H42\\u00b0  L27\\u00b0  41\\u00b0  Altamont  Cloudy  H37\\u00b0  L23\\u00b0  34\\u00b0  Athens  Light Rain  H41\\u00b0  L29\\u00b0  40\\u00b0  Benton  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Chatsworth  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Dalton  Fog  H43\\u00b0  L27\\u00b0  43\\u00b0  Dayton  Cloudy  H34\\u00b0  L22\\u00b0  32\\u00b0  Dunlap  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Murphy  Light Rain  H41\\u00b0  L29\\u00b0  40\\u00b0  Pikeville  Cloudy  H34\\u00b0  L22\\u00b0  32\\u00b0  Summerville  Cloudy  H48\\u00b0  L30\\u00b0  47\\u00b0  Ringgold  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0  Trenton  Cloudy  H43\\u00b0  L28\\u00b0  42\\u00b0        Jordan Chiles prepares to compete in the floor final at the Paris Olympics.      (CNN) -TheCourt of Arbitration for Sport (CAS)is standing by its ruling that Romania's Ana B\\u0103rbosu is the rightful third place finisher in floor exercise at the Paris Olympics.  The decision led the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to request that American gymnastJordan Chilesreturn the bronze medal she was originally awarded.  In a media release on Wednesday, CAS maintains that, during its hearing with Romanian and US officials, there was never a dispute over USA Gymnastics (USAG) missing the one-minute deadline to challenge Chiles' floor exercise score.  Olympic judges had inially revised Chiles' score, raising her into the bronze medal position and bumping B\\u0103rbosu off the podium.  \\\"At the hearing, there was no dispute between the parties that Ms. Chiles' inquiry was submitted 1 minute and 4 seconds after her score was official [sic] displayed on the scoreboard,\\\" CASsaidin its release.  \\\"All parties accepted as clear and determinative the report prepared by Omega, the official timekeeper for the Olympic Games, and submitted by the FIG itself. No party sought the admittance of other evidence.\\\"  USAG has previously stated that it did not come into possession of video which it claims proves that its inquiry was submitted after just 47 seconds until after CAS had already made its ruling.  \\\"The video footage provided was not available to USA Gymnastics prior to the tribunal's decision and thus USAG did not have the opportunity to previously submit it,\\\" USAG said Sunday.  The US Olympic & Paralympic Committee (USOPC) and USAG also now claim that CAS initially sent \\\"crucial communications\\\" to the wrong email addresses, and as a result, the parties were not able to properly prepare for the hearing.  \\\"The USOPC strongly contests the CAS decision due to significant procedural errors,\\\" USOPC told CNN Thursday. \\\"From August 6-9, CAS sent crucial communications to erroneous email addresses at USOPC and USAG, an error not corrected until August 9 - three days after filing, two days past the deadline to submit objections, and less than 24 hours before the hearing.  \\\"This deprived us of adequate time to respond meaningfully or gather necessary evidence. We informed CAS of our objections immediately.\\\"  Both parties say they will continue to appeal the matter.  \\\"Our pursuit of truth in this matter remains unwavering,\\\" the USOPC said.  On Monday, USA Gymnastics said it would \\\"continue to pursue every possible avenue and appeal process, including to the Swiss Federal Tribunal, to ensure the just scoring, placement, and medal award for Jordan.\\\"  Last week, Chiles posted four breaking hearts emojis on her Instagram story, explaining how she was \\\"taking this time and removing myself from social media for my mental health.\\\"  Local 3 News(@local3news) \\u2022 Instagram photos and videos  Your browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:  Get up-to-the-minute news sent straight to your device.\"}"